,"format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Nu\u2019man ibn Bashir reported: I asked Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, about His saying, \u201cRepent to Allah with sincere repentance,\u201d (66:8). Umar said, \u201cIt is a servant who repents from a sin and never commits it again.\u201d Source: Tafsi\u0304r al-T\u0323abari\u0304 23\/107 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33792,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/20\/hasan-never-forgot-his-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":26964,"position":1},"title":"Hasan on Fear: He enters Paradise because he never forgot his sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hisham ibn Hassan reported: Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cVerily, a man may commit a sin and he never forgets it, always fearing it, until he enters Paradise.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad ibn H\u0323anbal 1581 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0647\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0627\u0645 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u062d\u064e\u0633\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0635\u0631\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31716,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/02\/istighfar-salat-for-tawbah\/","url_meta":{"origin":26964,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Istighfar: Praying for repentance after committing a sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 2, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Bakr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo man commits a sin, then purifies himself in ablution, then prays, and then asks Allah for forgiveness, but that Allah will forgive him.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited this verse, \u201cThose who, if they behave immorally or wrong\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19656,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/08\/03\/istighfar-unless-you-stop-asking\/","url_meta":{"origin":26964,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Istighfar: Allah forgives you unless you stop asking","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Uqbah ibn 'Amir reported: A man came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, one of us has committed a sin.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cIt will be written against him.\u201d The man said, \u201cThen he has sought forgiveness and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40466,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/06\/07\/rizq-salat-zakat\/","url_meta":{"origin":26964,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wealth: Allah provides for charity, not indulgence","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 7, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Waqid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah said: Verily, We have sent down wealth for the performance of prayer and offering charity. If the son of Adam owned a valley, he would like to have a second. If he had two valleys,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17683,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/21\/umar-apostasy-riddah-murtad\/","url_meta":{"origin":26964,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Apostasy: I did not command it, I was not pleased","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn al-Qari reported: A man came to Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, from Abu Musa al-Ashari. Umar asked him about the people and he informed him. Then, Umar said, \u201cDo you have any recent news?\u201d Abu Musa said, \u201cYes, a man turned back to unbelief\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/26964","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\